 #23: \"PURIFICATION IS HALF OF FAITH ... \" .................................................. 709 SELECTED VOCABULARY ................................................................................................ 710 TAKHREEJ ................................................................................................................... 710 GENERAL COMMENTS ABOUT THIS HADITH ...................................................................... 711 ABOUT THE NARRATOR: AL-HAARITH IBN AASIM AL-ASHARI ................................................ 711 \"PURIFICATION IS HALF OF THE FAITH.\" ............................................................................ 712 \"THE PHRASE AL-HAMDUL/LLAH ('ALL PRAISE BE TO ALLAH') FILLS THE SCALE.\" ........................ 716 \"THE PHRASES SUBHAANALLAAH ('HIGH IS ALLAH ABOVE EVERY IMPERFECTION AND NEED; HE IS PURE AND PERFECT') AND AL-HAMDULILLAH ('ALL PRAISE BE TO ALLAH') TOGETHER FILL-OR EACH FILL-WHAT IS BETWEEN THE HEAVENS AND EARTH.\" ........................................................ 721 \"PRAYER IS A LIGHT.\" ................................................................................................... 725 \"CHARITY IS A PROOF.\" ................................................................................................. 728 \"PATIENCE IS A BRIGHTNESS.\" ........................................................................................ 732 \"THE QURAN IS EITHER AN ARGUMENT FOR OR AGAINST YOU.\" ............................................ 734 \"AND EVERYONE GOES OUT IN THE MORNING AND SELLS HIMSELF, EITHER FREEING OR DESTROYING HIMSELF.\" .................................................................................................................. 736 OTHER POINTS RELATED TO THIS HADITH ......................................................................... 738 ix Commentary on the 40 Hadith of al-Nawawi SUMMARY OF THE HADITH ............................................................................................ 739 HADITH #24: \"O MY SERVANTS, I HAVE FORBIDDEN WRONGDOING FOR MYSELF ... \" ............................................................................................................................... 741 SELECTED VOCABULARY .................................... ......... ................................................... 743 TAKHREEJ ................................................................................................................... 744 GENERAL COMMENTS ABOUT THIS HADITH ...................................................................... 745 ABOUT THE NARRATOR: ABU DHARR AL-GHIFAARI ............................................................. 745 FROM AMONG THE SAYINGS HE RELATES FROM HIS LORD (MAY HE BE GLORIFIED) .................... 745 \"0 MY SERVANTS\" ...................................................................................................... 751 \"I HAVE FORBIDDEN WRONGDOING (zulm) FOR MYSELF\" ................................................. 751 \"AND I HAVE MADE IT FORBIDDEN FOR YOU\" ..................................................................... 757 ''THEREFORE, DO NOT WRONG ONE ANOTHER.\" ................................................................. 767 \"Q MY SERVANTS, ALL OF YOU ARE LOST EXCEPT FOR THOSE WHOM I HAVE GUIDED.\" .............. 768 \"THEREFORE, SEEK GUIDANCE FROM ME AND I WILL GUIDE YOU.\" ........................................ 773 \"0 MY SERVANTS, ALL OF YOU ARE HUNGRY EXCEPT FOR THOSE WHOM I HAVE FED. THEREFORE, SEEK FOOD FROM ME AND I WILL FEED YOU.\" ....... ............................................................. 775 \"Q MY SERVANTS, ALL OF YOU ARE NAKED EXCEPT FOR THOSE WHOM I HAVE CLOTHED. THEREFORE, SEEK CLOTHING FROM ME AND I WILL CLOTHE YOU.\" .......................................................... 777 \"0 MY SERVANTS, YOU SIN BY NIGHT AND BY DAY, AND I FORGIVE ALL SINS. THEREFORE, SEEK FORGIVENESS FROM ME AND I WILL FORGIVE YOU.\" .....